#### Common

- avoid visual markers that do not correspond to sounds
- avoid acronyms

#### English

- omit capitalisation for Titles Made of Many Words, Corporations, Products, I,
  after a full stop, and generaly capitalise way less
- use capitalisation for names of persons, places, communities, and
  where an identity could feel disrespected by its omission

#### Italiano

- uso verbi intransitivi in maniera transitiva quando il significato Ã©
  chiaro, per esempio "scendi le chiavi"
- uso volentieri il tempo al futuro, il condizionale ed il "le"

